reviews.review_text: Miller Strikes Again Amazing SBD of a really good performance.  This run was a great farewell for the old rat-trap that was Boston Garden (having grown up there I was getting a little tired of obstructed view seats, terrible acoustics and the occasional rat).  Really strong show with a great Jack Straw opener setting the tone for the night and Bruce really giving it a huge kick in the pants.  Again, great quality on this one and many thanks.

vg show for most part Vg show overall. Though he's a wonderful player in general, Horsnby leaves me scratching my head some times. He absolutely butchers what could have been a beautiful BROKEDOWN PALACE, with his aggressive, loud and staccato accordian playing. Sometimes he just sticks out too much when he could do more service to the group by blending (or, in this case, not choosing a mid-heavy inappropriate instrument).
spacey very good show.  not as good as the night before, but very confident jamming, very spacey.  see dark stars in the second set.  the jam post second verse is absolutely a tinklin'.

Today is all about the Hornsby Absolutely one of the most BEAUTIFUL Jack Straw's..Cold Rain...Candyman..Mr.Hornsby on Keyboards..Even the Tuning is gorgeous
I saw this tour in Phx/Vegas/..Man they KILLED "Valley Road" and "The way it is"....

And Songs of   Our Own..... Charlie Miller !

I hope you have at least an inkling of hope of how much joy you;re brought to so many of of "Deadheads" out there....

Thank you SO much !  More than words can say,,,,,

Is this.... The BEST from 1991? I attended this show on my 31st birthday as a surprise it still remains the BEST birthday I've ever had. This entire run is very much worthy of a box set perhaps for 2015, HINT, HINT!!!!
